\par\tab Color
[as Integer or (R G B)]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]


[Method]
EndImage
[Function]
dcl_SlideView_EndImage
[Desc]
This method is used to store what has been drawn or painted to the SlideView’s paint able area to memory.  What this does is make all lines, arcs, text, etc. become part of the stored picture that the SlideView uses to paint from.  This method must be called after all objects have been drawn to the SlideView, or possible visual errors could occur, especially if another dialog box is moved over the SlideView and what has been drawn will be erased.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>


[Method]
SetHighLight
[Function]
dcl_SlideView_SetHighLight
[Desc]
This method draws a rectangle around the inside of the border as indication that the control has been selected or highlighted for some purpose. 
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab ColorIndex
[as Integer]


[Method]
RemoveHighLight
[Function]
dcl_SlideView_RemoveHighLight
[Desc]
This method removes the drawn rectangle around the inside of the border that indicates the control has been selected or highlighted for some purpose.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>


[End of File]